7. AI-Powered Self-Service: DataScout — The "Amazon-Like" Experience

Beyond building the Member DNA semantic layer, LatentView deployed DataScout, an AI-powered natural language query interface built on Databricks Genie, that sits on top of the Member DNA Gold layer and allows business users to interrogate member data by asking questions in plain English.

What DataScout Is:

A governed AI data room exposing 200+ key member attributes across member identity, demographics, enrollment, cost & utilization, risk scoring, clinical conditions, medication adherence, health equity, and mortality — all through a conversational interface. The AI automatically:

Interprets the intent — understands what the user is asking, even with imprecise terminology
Generates optimized SQL — writes the correct query with filters, aggregations, groupings, and case logic
Executes and returns results — delivers tabular data with row counts
Auto-generates visualizations — produces charts appropriate to the data shape
Provides narrative summaries — explains the results in natural language
How DataScout Was Built:

Data Preparation — The 635+ column Member DNA table was decomposed into focused, denormalized analytical views and curated to 200+ key attributes. Every column was annotated with business-friendly descriptions in Unity Catalog, authored jointly by LatentView engineers and Blue Shield SMEs.

Knowledge Store — A structured intelligence layer encoding Blue Shield's business logic: standardized SQL expressions for measures like PMPM, risk scores, and adherence rates; filters like "active members" and "high-risk cohort"; vetted example queries; and prompt matching rules for abbreviations, misspellings, and date expressions. Synonyms ensured varied terminology across teams all resolves correctly.

Benchmarking and Iteration — A benchmark suite of test questions with verified SQL answers, run regularly to track accuracy. Curation followed an iterative cycle: seed, test with SMEs, review auto-suggested improvements from knowledge mining, and promote approved changes.

Monitoring and Governance — Space managers review interactions via the Monitoring tab, triage flagged responses, and track adoption through audit logs. DataScout inherits Unity Catalog governance — access controls and data classification propagate automatically, keeping PHI protected.

What Users Can Ask DataScout:

"How many members by Finance LOB for current study period?"
"Show age distribution by age bands (0-17, 18-25, ... 65+)"
"What is the average PMPM for Medicare members in Q4 2025?"
"Which regions have the lowest statin adherence rates?"
"Show me the top 10 conditions by prevalence for members under 65"
The DataScout Vision for MetLife:

Ask "How many members enrolled in Group Life products in Q1 2026 by region?" and get instant answers
Ask "What is the age and gender distribution of our Medicare Advantage members?" without waiting for an analyst
